trace.\\n   - Set the `condition` field to `{ \\\"typeReached\\\": \\\"<class>\\\" }`, where `<class>` is the first class on the stack trace whose package shares the leading namespace with the tested library's package.\\n   - Package overlap can be partial, full package equality is not required.\\n   - Example: tested library's group `org.hibernate.orm...` and the class from a stack trace `org.hibernate.resource...` is a valid match.\\n\\n5. Verify and iterate:\\n   - Run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<coordinates>` again.\\n   - If another missing entry appears, repeat from step 2.\\n   - Finish only when the test run succeeds.\\n\\n## Error Patterns\\n\\nUse this reference when deriving the missing entry and condition.\\n\\n### Missing Registration Entry Pattern\\n\\nExample error shape:\\n\\n```text\\nCaused by: org.graalvm.nativeimage.MissingReflectionRegistrationError:\\nCannot reflectively invoke constructor 'public org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator()'\\n...\\nadd the following to the 'reflection' section of reachability-metadata.json:\\n{\\n  \\\"type\\\": \\\"org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator\\\",\\n  \\\"methods\\\": [{ \\\"name\\\": \\\"<init>\\\", \\\"parameterTypes\\\": [] }]\\n}\\n...\\nat org.hibernate.boot.model.internal.GeneratorBinder.instantiateGeneratorViaDefaultConstructor(...)\\nat org.hibernate.resource.beans.internal.Helper$2.produceBeanInstance(...)\\n```\\n\\n### Condition Inference\\n\\nFor missing type `org.hibernate.id.enhanced.SequenceStyleGenerator`, a valid condition class is:\\n\\n`org.hibernate.boot.model.internal.GeneratorBinder`\\n\\nReason: both share the leading namespace `org.hibernate`, which is sufficient for this workflow.\\n\\n## Environment Troubleshooting\\n\\n- If failures look unrelated or tooling looks inconsistent, verify both `JAVA_HOME` and `GRAALVM_HOME` point to a compatible GraalVM JDK distribution.\\n- If they are not set to GraalVM, ask the user to provide the correct GraalVM distribution path and retry.\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n95:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_54\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"I’m past the repository-structure issue and now working the actual native-image failure. The next step is to inspect `akka.actor.ActorSystemImpl` and compare it to existing metadata patterns so we can add the smallest reflection entry that unblocks Scala’s lazy-val initialization without broad over-registration.\"}}\n101:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_57\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"javap -classpath ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/com.typesafe.akka/akka-actor_3/2.6.21/*/akka-actor_3-2.6.21.jar -private akka.actor.ActorSystemImpl | sed -n '1,260p'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"Compiled from \\\"ActorSystem.scala\\\"\\npublic class akka.actor.ActorSystemImpl extends akka.actor.ExtendedActorSystem {\\n  public static final long OFFSET$0;\\n  public long 0bitmap$1;\\n  private final java.lang.String name;\\n  private final java.lang.ClassLoader classLoader;\\n  private final scala.Option guardianProps;\\n  private final long uid;\\n  private volatile scala.Option<akka.actor.ActorRef> logDeadLetterListener;\\n  private final akka.actor.DynamicAccess _dynamicAccess;\\n  private final akka.actor.ActorSystem$Settings settings;\\n  private final akka.dispatch.MonitorableThreadFactory threadFactory;\\n  private final akka.event.EventStream eventStream;\\n  private final akka.event.LoggingFilter logFilter;\\n  public final akka.event.MarkerLoggingAdapter akka$actor$ActorSystemImpl$$markerLogging;\\n  private final akka.event.LoggingAdapter log;\\n  private final akka.actor.Scheduler scheduler;\\n  private final akka.actor.ActorRefProvider provider;\\n  private final akka.dispatch.Mailboxes mailboxes;\\n  private final akka.dispatch.Dispatchers dispatchers;\\n  private final scala.concurrent.ExecutionContextExecutor dispatcher;\\n  private final a