rn getProject().file(CoordinateUtils.replace(\\\"tests/src/$group$/$artifact$/\\\" + testVersion, parsedCoordinates)).toPath();\\n    }\\n\\n    private List<MetadataVersionsIndexEntry> readIndexEntries(Path indexFile) throws IOException {\\n        return objectMapper.readValue(indexFile.toFile(), new TypeReference<>() {});\\n    }\\n\\n    private Set<String> discoverTestResources(Path testsDirectory) throws IOException {\\n        Set<String> resources = new LinkedHashSet<>();\\n        Path resourceRoot = testsDirectory.resolve(\\\"src/test/resources\\\");\\n        if (!Files.isDirectory(resourceRoot)) {\\n            return resources;\\n        }\\n        try (var pathStream = Files.walk(resourceRoot)) {\\n            pathStream.filter(Files::isRegularFile)\\n                    .map(resourceRoot::relativize)\\n                    .map(Path::toString)\\n                    .map(this::normalizeResourcePath)\\n                    .forEach(resources::add);\\n        }\\n\\n        return resources;\\n    }\\n\\n    private void splitReflection(ObjectNode source, ObjectNode moved, Set<String> testPackages) {\\n        splitTypeKeyedArray(source, moved, \\\"reflection\\\", testPackages);\\n    }\\n\\n    private void splitSerialization(ObjectNode source, ObjectNode moved, Set<String> testPackages) {\\n        splitTypeKeyedArray(source, moved, \\\"serialization\\\", testPackages);\\n    }\\n\\n    private void splitTypeKeyedArray(ObjectNode source, ObjectNode moved, String fieldName, Set<String> testPackages) {\\n        JsonNode field = source.get(fieldName);\\n        if (!(field instanceof ArrayNode sourceEntries)) {\\n            return;\\n        }\\n\\n        ArrayNode keptEntries = objectMapper.createArrayNode();\\n        ArrayNode movedEntries = objectMapper.createArrayNode();\\n        for (JsonNode entry : sourceEntries) {\\n            if (isTestOnlyEntry(entry, testPackages)) {\\n                movedEntries.add(entry.deepCopy());\\n            } else {\\n                keptEntries.add(entry);\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        applySplitResult(source, moved, fieldName, keptEntries, movedEntries);\\n    }\\n\\n    private boolean isTestOnlyEntry(JsonNode entry, Set<String> testPackages) {\\n        if (entry == null || !entry.isObject()) {\\n            return false;\\n        }\\n        if (typeReferencesTestPackage(entry.get(\\\"type\\\"), testPackages)) {\\n            return true;\\n        }\\n        JsonNode condition = entry.get(\\\"condition\\\");\\n        if (condition != null && condition.isObject()) {\\n            JsonNode typeReached = condition.get(\\\"typeReached\\\");\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/software.amazon.awssdk:sqs:2.34.0/local-ci-fixup/run-consecutive-tests-2026-05-08T02-58-55-420191Z.log:48:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_25\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc \\\"rg -n \\\\\\\"splitTestOnlyMetadata|test-only|testOnly|reachability-metadata.json|empty metadata|user-code-filter\\\\\\\" docs tests/tck-build-logic src .github -g '\\\"'!**/build/**'\\\"'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"rg: src: No such file or directory (os error 2)\\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/scaffold/build.gradle.template:24:                userCodeFilterPath = \\\"user-code-filter.json\\\"\\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/FixTestNativeImageRun.java:37:    private static final String REACHABILITY_METADATA_FILE = \\\"reachability-metadata.json\\\";\\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/FixTestNativeImageRun.java:91:        // Ensure the tests build.gradle has an agent block; if not, create user-code-filter.json and add the agent block.\\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/scaffold/build.gradle.groovy.template:32:                userCodeFilterPath = \\\"user-code-filter.json\\\"\\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/resources/scaffold/build.gradle.scala3